author: scheu
msg: Added the changes to support the new JSR 101 v0.6 Enumeration code
for both Java2WSDL and WSDL2Java:
- base types other than String now work.
- changes to the EnumSerializer to deal with nil=true
- changes to the EnumSerializer to use new Enumeration methods
- added a isJavaID(...) method to JavaUtils which determines if a name can
be a valid java name (i.e. does not collide with keywords and has
appropriate characters)
- additional types added to the comprehensive types test.

author: butek
msg: This fixes a couple import problems reported by Thomas Sandholm
(sandholm@mcs.anl.gov)
- relative import file names were relative to the command line directory, not relative
to the file from which they were imported.
- faults appearing in imported files weren't generated.
Along with this fix I did 2 things:
- changed the import test to test these new conditions
- added a main to Emitter.java so that I can create the symbol table without generating
code.  This is a useful debugging tool, but I don't think we want this to be a documented
feature of AXIS.
